.TH GITFLOWER 1 "July 2026" "gitflower 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gitflower \- git-based development platform
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gitflower
[\fB\-\-config\fR \fIFILE\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gitflower
provides branch workflow enforcement via git hooks and a web UI for
browsing hosted bare repositories.
.PP
Per-repository commands act on the git repository in the current working
directory; hosting commands act on the repos directory from the global
configuration.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Report the branch rules in effect for the current bare repository. Writes
nothing: a repository with no \fBgitflower.*\fR keys is governed by the
built-in defaults.
.TP
.B install
Install the pre-receive hook into the current bare repository. Refuses to
overwrite a foreign hook unless \fB\-\-force\fR is given.
.TP
.B uninstall
Remove gitflower-owned hooks.
.TP
.B config show \fR[\fB\-\-global\fR]
Print the current repository's effective gitflower settings, or the server
configuration with \fB\-\-global\fR.
.TP
.B config edit
Open the repository's git config in an editor and validate the result.
.TP
.B create \fIPATH\fR
Create a bare repository under the configured repos directory.
Organization folders nest: \fBgitflower create org/team/app.git\fR.
.TP
.B list \fR[\fB\-\-format\fR table|json|yaml] [\fB\-\-warnings\fR]
List repositories in the repos directory.
.TP
.B web \fR[\fB\-\-addr\fR \fIADDRESS\fR]
Start the web server. Every endpoint serves JSON, a full HTML page, and
an HTML fragment from the same URL via content negotiation.
.TP
.B review \fR[\fB\-\-branch\fR \fIBRANCH\fR] [\fB\-\-base\fR \fIREF\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-tui\fR] [\fB\-\-empty\-review\fR] [\fB\-o\fR \fIPATH\fR]
Review a branch: scaffold a \fI.review\fR covering everything changed since
the last \fB[Review]\fR merge (falling back to \fImain\fR) and open the
review TUI. The review is stored on the \fIrefs/notes/reviews\fR notes ref,
keyed by the reviewed tip commit; \fB\-o\fR mirrors it to a file.
\fB\-\-no\-tui\fR scaffolds, saves, and prints where the review went.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I <bare-repo>/config
Per-repository branch rules, protection policy and branch display settings,
under \fB[gitflower]\fR. Only the repository's own config is read — never
\fI~/.gitconfig\fR or the system config.
.TP
.I ~/.config/gitflower/config.yaml, /etc/gitflower/config.yaml
Server configuration: repos directory and web address. The first file
found wins; \fB$GITFLOWER_CONFIG\fR or \fB\-\-config\fR override.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GITFLOWER_CONFIG
Path to the global configuration file.
.TP
.B GITFLOWER_BIN
Used by the installed hook shim to locate the gitflower executable.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git (1),
.BR githooks (5)
